  "title": "Sales & Market Development Executive – Awning (Mass Market Focus)",
  "description": "<p>We are an established awning manufacturer and supplier, expanding into the lower-end / mass-market segment.We are looking for a hands-on sales professional who understands real market pricing, cost pressure, and margin control—not theory.<br /></p><p>Primary responsibility is to drive growth in mass-market awning sales. Manage market pricing, gross margins, sales budgets, and operating and installation costs. Build and oversee sales channels including renovation contractors, small builders, and direct end-customers. Own the full sales cycle from lead generation and quotation through negotiation and closing. Work closely with operations to maintain cost discipline and ensure installation scopes are practical and achievable.</p><p>This role suits a commercially sharp, practical salesperson who understands real-world market conditions, is comfortable selling in a price-sensitive environment, and brings an entrepreneurial mindset focused on building value, not just closing deals.<br /></p><p>After 6–12 months, candidates who demonstrate stable sales, strong margin control, and a deep understanding of the business may progress to a profit-sharing arrangement or a joint venture focused on the mass-market segment.</p>",
